#  Energy Price Monitoring AI Platform

A real-time electricity price monitoring platform with AI-powered anomaly detection and natural language explanations.

## What it does
- Fetches electricity spot prices from the Energinet API (DK1 area)
- Detects anomalies using Isolation Forest (scikit-learn)
- Exposes a REST API built with Flask
- Stores results in a SQLite database
- Explains findings in plain English using Groq (Llama 3)

## Tech Stack
- Python, Flask, pandas, scikit-learn
- SQLite for storage
- Groq API (Llama 3) for AI explanations
- HTML, CSS, JavaScript + Chart.js for frontend
- Docker for containerization

## How to run
1. Clone the repo
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/OliverThybo/energy-ai-platform.git
   ```
2. Install dependencies
   ```
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```
3. Create a `.env` file and add your Groq API key
   ```
   GROQ_API_KEY=your_key_here
   ```
4. Run the app
   ```
   python -m api.app
   ```
5. Open your browser at `http://localhost:5000`

## API Endpoints
| Endpoint | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `GET /` | Frontend dashboard |
| `GET /prices` | Fetch, analyze and store latest prices |
| `GET /results` | Get stored results from database |
| `GET /explain` | Get AI explanation of latest analysis |

## Project Structure
```
energy-ai-platform/
├── data_ingestion/      # Fetches data from Energinet API
├── preprocessing/       # Cleans and formats data
├── model/               # Anomaly detection + AI explanation
├── api/                 # Flask REST API + frontend
├── db.py                # SQLite database logic
├── Dockerfile           # Container configuration
└── requirements.txt     # Python dependencies
```

